There is also some stack ordering strangeness in the overlay if you have multiple items in the overlay and a subtree with an OverlayPortal is moved with a global key. In the example below press in order: Button1, Button2, Button3, and finally reparent. Notice how the blue square jumps to the top.

This is likely related to how the items in the overlay are removed and re-added on deactivate and activate.

_EDIT: Just saw, this limitation is already mentioned in the PR description..._

